1
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:10,860
Does it still hurt?

2
00:01:11,360 --> 00:01:14,020
Did those troublemakers from last time do this?

3
00:01:14,360 --> 00:01:15,760
Don't make wild guesses.

4
00:01:16,240 --> 00:01:17,039
Let me ask you.

5
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:20,000
The delayed relocation funds

6
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:21,080
and the unauthorized modifications,

7
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:22,480
what exactly is going on?

8
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:23,640
Funds are tight.

9
00:01:23,960 --> 00:01:25,820
It's a delay, not a refusal to pay.

10
00:01:26,080 --> 00:01:27,410
Even if funds are tight,

11
00:01:27,760 --> 00:01:29,120
we can't shortchange the common people.

12
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:31,120
Do you know how hard their lives are?

13
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,090
Here we go again.

14
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,640
Okay, whatever you say.

15
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:38,200
Your unauthorized modifications to shrink the area

16
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,080
not only damage the company's reputation,

17
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:42,479
but also harm the interests of the common people.

18
00:01:42,479 --> 00:01:44,320
They are just a few commoners.

19
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,200
How much trouble can they cause?

20
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,320
I am a commoner.

21
00:01:48,479 --> 00:01:50,740
I come from the most ordinary commoners.

22
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:51,720
You people...

23
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:53,759
Why do you always look down on us?

24
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,240
Qiming.

25
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,520
How could I look down on you?

26
00:01:59,039 --> 00:02:00,570
You know how much I love you.

27
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:01,800
If you love me,

28
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:03,200
promise me

29
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:04,640
to rebuild.

30
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,960
Do you know how much money we'll lose if we rebuild?

31
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:11,280
If we finish building the houses and can't sell them,

32
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:12,320
the loss will be even greater.

33
00:02:12,320 --> 00:02:13,600
Most people have already signed.

34
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,600
We won't have trouble selling them.

35
00:02:16,320 --> 00:02:17,760
When these buyers

36
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,000
come to the company to cause trouble later,

37
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:19,800
and the authorities investigate,

38
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:21,730
neither of us will get away with it.

39
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,460
I'll ask you one last time.

40
00:02:24,079 --> 00:02:26,010
Are you going to listen to me or not?

41
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:35,660
I'll listen to you.

42
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:50,820
Lao Jin.

43
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,040
Great. I was just looking for you.

44
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:53,840
Is the report out?

45
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:54,400
Yes.

46
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,520
The victim died of carbon monoxide poisoning.

47
00:02:56,520 --> 00:02:58,520
The fingerprint we lifted from the scene

48
00:02:58,520 --> 00:02:59,579
belongs to Lu Yang.

49
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,400
Lu Yang's?

50
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:03,250
He turned it on himself?

51
00:03:03,640 --> 00:03:05,040
Then the fingerprint on the bottle at the scene

52
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:07,160
must belong to the liquor delivery girl.

53
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:07,920
Get back to work, Lao Jin.

54
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:08,520
Your colleagues are waiting for you.

55
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:09,040
Thanks.

56
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:09,680
Good work.

57
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:10,360
Sir.

58
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:11,320
Li.

59
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:13,560
Sir.

60
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,000
I've finished checking.

61
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,880
The shoe size is 43.

62
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,160
The tire tracks don't show much,

63
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:21,160
but it's definitely not a cheap car.

64
00:03:24,760 --> 00:03:25,520
It seems that

65
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,560
someone did come over last night.

66
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:27,920
Yes.

67
00:03:28,079 --> 00:03:29,920
He called for a liquor delivery girl last night.

68
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:30,960
Here is the phone number.

69
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:31,490
Call back

70
00:03:32,040 --> 00:03:32,680
and say

71
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:34,840
we want some liquor.

72
00:03:34,840 --> 00:03:35,240
Okay.

73
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,280
The project in the western suburbs,

74
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,600
must be won by you.

75
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:41,840
With it in Ye Qiming's hands,

76
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,680
I don't feel at ease.

77
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:48,640
Since I could win the eastern suburbs,

78
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:50,770
the western suburbs must also be mine.

79
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:54,040
Let's see what you can do.

80
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:01,520
Name.

81
00:04:02,040 --> 00:04:02,700
Liu Xiaoju.

82
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:03,360
Age.

83
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,820
You saw Lu Yang last night, right?

84
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:10,920
Did something happen to Lu Yang?

85
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:13,720
If something really happened to him,

86
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:15,250
it has nothing to do with me.

87
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:18,399
Why would you think something happened to him?

88
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,459
Just guessing.

89
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:21,399
Why else would I be here?

90
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:24,050
Did you know Lu Yang is dead?

91
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,840
Lu Yang is dead?

92
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:30,080
Wait.

93
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:32,520
You don't think I killed him, do you?

94
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:33,720
I didn't kill anyone.

95
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,000
I couldn't have killed Lu Yang.

96
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,240
Why would I kill him?

97
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:37,260
Tell the truth.

98
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,370
What exactly did Lu Yang do?

99
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,560
I don't know.

100
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:44,240
How did you guys meet?

101
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,280
I just delivered liquor to him.

102
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:48,610
After a few deliveries,

103
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:50,640
we gradually got to know each other.

104
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:52,760
So Lu Yang is very rich?

105
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:54,200
Him?

106
00:04:55,560 --> 00:04:57,090
Sometimes he is quite rich.

107
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:58,080
Sometimes,

108
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:59,650
he is completely broke.

109
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:02,720
I often see people coming to ask him for money anyway.

110
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,980
I suspect he owes a lot of money out there.

111
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,840
Why did you bring him alcohol yesterday?

112
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:08,920
He told me to.

113
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:10,760
He messaged me saying

114
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:11,800
the tip would be doubled.

115
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:12,800
Why wouldn't I go?

116
00:05:13,200 --> 00:05:14,600
Who would say no to money?

117
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:18,290
What time did you get there and when did you leave?

118
00:05:19,640 --> 00:05:20,880
Around

119
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,200
10 o'clock.

120
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,000
I only stayed for an hour.

121
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,560
During that hour,

122
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,080
was there anything unusual about him?

123
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,120
Nothing unusual.

124
00:05:32,159 --> 00:05:33,360
He told me something.

125
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,720
He told me he would have money soon.

126
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:37,840
Could settle all the debts outside.

127
00:05:38,159 --> 00:05:39,490
But he always says that.

128
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:40,960
I didn't take it seriously.

129
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:42,200
So when you went there,

130
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:44,130
was the gas stove on in the kitchen?

131
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,080
Gas stove?

132
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:47,800
Do you think I would notice that?

133
00:05:50,680 --> 00:05:52,280
Anyway, when I entered the house,

134
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,540
I didn't smell any gas.

135
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,760
Tell us what happened yesterday

136
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:55,880
in detail.

137
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,280
Yesterday.

138
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:07,920
You called me over

139
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:10,100
just to treat me like this?

140
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:22,130
Why so proactive today?

141
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:24,520
I'm happy today.

142
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:26,560
So happy?

143
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:30,240
Because I'm getting money soon.

144
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:32,720
Money again?

145
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:36,020
You said that last time and the time before that.

146
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,120
Where's the money?

147
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:39,120
I'm really getting money this time.

148
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:42,320
Okay, you're getting money.

149
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:43,560
Come on.

150
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:51,420
Where is this money

151
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:53,020
coming from this time?

152
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,080
Open the wine, open the wine.

153
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:12,760
Cheers.

154
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:14,690
Have a drink.

155
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:32,480
Lu Yang.

156
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,280
Wake up.

157
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,420
I haven't paid the tip yet.

158
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:51,240
Great.

159
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:52,770
We have money again.

160
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:55,320
I will have more money.

161
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:02,560
Lu Yang.

162
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,530
Remember to come tomorrow.

163
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,960
As long as you have money,

164
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:15,090
as long as you're alive.

165
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:22,040
Then I took the money and left.

166
00:08:22,360 --> 00:08:24,160
He was just drunk at that time.

167
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:27,480
Did you meet anyone else when you went there?

168
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,040
No.

169
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,880
They promised to give us the demolition compensation today.

170
00:08:35,880 --> 00:08:37,400
There's still no news.

171
00:08:37,799 --> 00:08:40,530
I don't think the general manager would lie to us.

172
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,420
What are you doing?

173
00:08:59,360 --> 00:08:59,890
Alright.

174
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:01,680
Listen up.

175
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:03,680
What demolition compensation?

176
00:09:03,680 --> 00:09:05,560
This is your demolition compensation.

177
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:06,090
Let's go.

178
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,680
Nobody move.

179
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:10,860
Don't move.

180
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:33,280
What is it?

181
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:35,880
Give me the distribution plan

182
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:37,810
for the demolition compensation.

183
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:38,680
Tomorrow.

184
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:39,640
No.

185
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,200
I already promised to pay them tomorrow.

186
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:42,680
Hurry up

187
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,280
and have them get it done.

188
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,120
Thank you. Thank you.

189
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,920
It's not that easy.

190
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,000
It's not a small sum.

191
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,440
It's been a year since the demolition.

192
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:53,240
You should have paid them a long time ago.

193
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:55,520
What you're doing is illegal and against the rules.

194
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:57,320
Are you trying to send me to jail?

195
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,400
Why haven't you left yet?

196
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,360
Okay, I'll go right now.

197
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,280
Let me ask you,

198
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:12,560
why didn't you construct according to the blueprints?

199
00:10:12,560 --> 00:10:14,420
The land costs millions per acre.

200
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:16,400
How can we make money if we don't shrink the dimensions?

201
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:19,200
Is our company's reputation only worth this much?

202
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:20,640
It's not as serious as you make it sound.

203
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:22,360
All companies do it this way.

204
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,920
We live in a society governed by law now.

205
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:27,280
Anyone who deceives consumers,

206
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:29,000
and anyone who deceives farmers,

207
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,040
will not end well.

208
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:32,120
The law shows no mercy, you know?

209
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,480
What are you laughing at?

210
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:38,400
You look so cute when you're being serious.

211
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:39,120
What's cute about it?

212
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:40,520
I can't lose my conscience just for being cute,

213
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:41,240
and scam the common people.

214
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:43,000
That's my bottom line, you know?

215
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,080
Then give me a kiss.

216
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:45,200
Kiss you?

217
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:47,770
We're at the company, how could I kiss you?

218
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,280
I can kiss you.

219
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,860
But you have to promise me.

220
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:57,480
Is the demolition compensation ready?

221
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:00,820
Tear down those houses and rebuild them.

222
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:05,320
Go now.

223
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,120
Go quickly.

224
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,320
Got it.

225
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:09,360
I promised them.

226
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:10,720
Be good.

227
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,560
We can't get beaten up

228
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,520
for nothing today.

229
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:26,120
Tomorrow,

230
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:27,200
let my brother take us

231
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,600
to find that capitalist.

232
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:29,480
Let's go find him.

233
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:30,960
Let's go.

234
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:32,520
Did peeling hurt your hand?

235
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,320
It hurts here.

236
00:11:35,080 --> 00:11:36,560
Ma'am, you look so young.

237
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:38,570
What are you talking about?

238
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:41,160
You helped us husk the corn.

239
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,690
Your hands must be hurting.

240
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:43,560
It's nothing,

241
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:44,520
sister.

242
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:46,640
Recently,

243
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,760
have any strangers moved in?

244
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:51,200
Or anyone acting weird?

245
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,440
We have all kinds of people living here.

246
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:57,280
There are quite a few weird ones.

247
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:58,520
But...

248
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,700
There is actually one,

249
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:02,680
he looks quite honest.

250
00:12:02,920 --> 00:12:05,240
He has been hanging around this area lately.

251
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:06,040
Right, right.

252
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,360
Look at my memory.

253
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:08,560
This guy is

254
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,200
tall and thin.

255
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:11,580
Where does he live?

256
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:12,400
He lives in

257
00:12:12,840 --> 00:12:14,640
old Mr. Deng's house over there.

258
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:15,440
Just the one in front,

259
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:15,970
that one.

260
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,440
The one with the pomegranate tree?

261
00:12:17,440 --> 00:12:18,040
Right.

262
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:21,840
How did it go?

263
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:23,320
It's done.

264
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,480
No traces were left.

265
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:27,960
Well done.

266
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:31,890
Why do I feel like

267
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:33,840
there is a mysterious

268
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:35,940
and evil force in our company?

269
00:12:38,360 --> 00:12:39,890
What are you talking about?

270
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,160
Those relocated households got into a car accident

271
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,160
on their way here.

272
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:46,020
The point is, someone also threatened them.

273
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:46,720
No, no.

274
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:48,400
How are they doing now?

275
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,580
They've all gone home.

276
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:55,380
Those farmers are so pitiful.

277
00:12:57,760 --> 00:12:58,320
Qiming,

278
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:00,480
how about this?

279
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:02,000
Let's go withdraw the money now

280
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,060
and give it to them.

281
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:04,620
You decide.

282
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:05,850
Don't worry.

283
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,720
I'll call the bank right now.

284
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:14,520
Hello, Liu.

285
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:16,640
Prepare one million in cash immediately.

286
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:17,700
We'll go pick it up.

287
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:23,170
What are you waiting for? Let's go.

288
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:28,360
Master, Captain Shen,

289
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:30,170
over there, the third room.

290
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:49,100
This doesn't look like someone just lived here.

291
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:51,520
